<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/14.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-11"><hi rend="italic">April 11,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Beaupré asks if permission has been obtained from Belgium for the
                            transit of Nicholas Knepper in accordance with article 4 of the Belgian
                            law of 1874.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>